Title: UCLA's Delta Zeta quartet singing for Ronald Reagan, Hollywood Bowl, Los Angeles, 1957
Description.caption: Text from newspaper caption: Bowl Warmup--Delta Zeta quartet gives MC Ronald Reagan burst of song in warmup for UCLA's spring sing at Hollywood Bowl.  From left, Mary Upton, Rachel Cadwalader, Elena Redmond, Sally Sutton.
Description.note: Ladies of the Delta Zeta quartet from UCLA singing for actor Ronald Reagan at the Hollywood Bowl in Los Angeles.|~|This photograph appears with the article "Delta Zeta's Chorus Wins Sing at Bowl," Los Angeles Times, 4 May 1957: pg. 2.
Description.fundingNote: Access to this collection is generously supported by Haynes Foundation funds.

Title: Bugle Corps members at the funeral for Grace Lowe and Morris Lowe, Los Angeles, 1964
Description.caption: Text from newspaper caption: Paying their respects-Girls of the Senoritas Drum and Bugle Corps are in costume as they line up at chapel for funeral of two bus crash victims. At right center is Philip Kwan, director of the Chinese Drum and Bugle Corps.
